16-Jun-2002 Released Kopete 0.4.1
=================================

o Main App
	o Now it uses standard KDE method to load plugins (Faure, Simon, Martijn)
	 
o ICQ Plugin
	o New ICQ-Userinfo Dialog, now tabbed and more infos (Stefan)
	o Make 'Web Awareness' and 'Hide IP' configurable (Stefan)

o MSN Plugin
	o Updated protocol due to Microsoft server changes (Duncan)

01-Jun-2002 Released Kopete 0.4
==============================

o Main App
	o Kopete API redesign/cleanup (Ryan)
	o Added globally Away/Available (Duncan)
	o Added Auto-Away Plugin (Duncan)
	o KNotify beep support for KopeteEvent (Hendrik)
	o KNotify sound support for KopeteEvent (Hendrik)	
	o KopeteMessageManager support (Duncan, Daniel)
          - All plugins inherits events (balloon, etc)
          - All plugins use the same chat dialog
          - API allows for multiuser chat
	o Emoticons can be disabled now. (Duncan) 

o IRC Plugin
	o Updated for globally Away/Vailable
	o Added support for: (Nick)
		o /server
		o Loading a console at IRC plugin load
		o Turning on/off left side icons in chat messages
		o Turning on/off timestamping
		o Colors, bold, and underlining in messages
		o Ability to load more than one console
	o Many bug fixes (Nick)
	o Removed servers from the contact list. They were intrusive. (Nick)
	o Channels and private conversation windows only appear 
	  in the contact list when added using "Add Contact" (Nick)

o ICQ Plugin
	 o Updated for globally Away/Available (Duncan)
	 o Added support for authorizing contacts (Duncan)
	 o Added support for invisible status ( Duncan )
o MSN Plugin
	o Updated for globally Away/Available (Duncan)
	o Big Protocol cleanup and plugin redesign (Martijn)

o AIM Plugin
	 o Updated for globally Away/Available (Duncan)

o Jabber Plugin
	 o First release of Kopete with Jabber
           , numerous updates. (Daniel)

o Yahoo Plugin
	o Introduced Yahoo plugin

05-04-2002 Released Kopete 0.3
==============================

o Main App

	o Event Notifier
		o Balloon Style (Duncan)
		o Flashing Tray Style (Duncan)
	o History Widget (Richard)
	o XML History Logger (Ryan)
	o Emoticons, Emoticons Themes (Duncan)

o IRC Plugin

	o Misc Enhancements (Nick)
	o Tabbed UI (Nick)
	o /msg, /nick, and proper /part support.
	o Query window support
	o More error checking
	o The IRC plugin will not be included in this release
	  as it lacks functionality and stability still. It
	  may be included in the near future.

o ICQ Plugin

	o ICQ Engine
		o Uses KExtendedSocket now (Herwin Steehouwer)

	o Contact move (Duncan)
	o Notifier support (Duncan)
	o History support (Richard)
	o Hide offline contacts (Stefan)

o MSN Plugin

	o Hiding offline contacts (Stefan)


